rlm-gar-open

Browse all container images across one or more GCP projects via an
fzf picker and open the selected image in the Artifact Registry
console. Projects come from $GAR_SEARCH_PROJECTS (colon-separated).

Images are fetched from all DOCKER repositories in each project via
the Artifact Registry packages.list REST endpoint (one API call per
repo). Results are cached in ~/.cache/gar-open/; selecting
--- REFRESH CACHE --- opens a secondary fzf picker (TAB to
multi-select) where you choose which projects to re-fetch — entries
for un-picked projects are preserved in the cache.

The picker is sorted by most-recently-used (history kept in
~/.cache/gar-open/history.txt). On confirmation, prints the fully
qualified image path and the GCP console URL, copies the URL to the
clipboard, and opens it in the browser.

GCR layer-cache pseudo-packages (<image>/cache) are filtered out.

ENVIRONMENT
  GAR_SEARCH_PROJECTS
              Colon-separated list of GCP project IDs to browse.
              Required; the function errors out if not set.

REQUIRES
  gcloud, fzf, jq, curl, python3 (for URL-decoding package names).

NOTE
  OSC 8 hyperlinks in the preview pane require a terminal emulator
  that supports them (Kitty, Ghostty, iTerm2, WezTerm). Inside tmux
  also set: set -ga terminal-features "*:hyperlinks"
